 Norfolk, England":"英国諾福爾可艾爾平加姆","St. Margaret Churchyard, Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"英国英格兰諾福爾可費爾布利格","lifeSummary":"Sir Simon le Bigod是Sir Roger Bigod Felbrigge的儿子，于1274年出生在英国諾福爾可費爾布利格。他于1315年与Alice Thorpe在英国英格兰諾福爾可費爾布利格结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1351年在英国英格兰諾福爾可費爾布利格享年77岁，埋葬在英国英格兰諾福爾可費爾布利格。"},"hr":{"1274–1351":"1274.–1351.","1288–1320":"1288–1320","1290–1317":"1290–1317.","1316–1380":"1316.–1380","1254–1306":"1254–1306","1274":"1274.","1351":"1351.","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1316":"1316.","1315":"1315.","1337":"1337","from 1275 to 1306":"od 1275. do 1306.","1453":"1453","1288":"1288","1254":"1254","1320":"1320","1317":"1317.","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","Felbrigg, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, Erpingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, England","St. Margaret Churchyard, Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1274–1351":"1274–1351","1288–1320":"1288–1320","1290–1317":"1290–1317","1316–1380":"1316–1380","1254–1306":"1254–1306","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","from 1275 to 1306":"od 1275 do 1306","1453":"1453","1288":"1288","1254":"1254","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","Felbrigg, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, Erpingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, Anglie","St. Margaret Churchyard, Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1274–1351":"1274–1351","1288–1320":"1288–1320","1290–1317":"1290–1317","1316–1380":"1316–1380","1254–1306":"1254–1306","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","from 1275 to 1306":"fra 1275 til 1306","1453":"1453","1288":"1288","1254":"1254","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","Felbrigg, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, Erpingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, England","St. Margaret Churchyard, Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1274–1351":"1274–1351","1288–1320":"1288–1320","1290–1317":"1290–1317","1316–1380":"1316–1380","1254–1306":"1254–1306","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","from 1275 to 1306":"van 1275 to 1306","1453":"1453","1288":"1288","1254":"1254","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","Felbrigg, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Felbrigg, Erpingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, England","St. Margaret Churchyard, Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1274–1351":"1274–1351","1288–1320":"1288–1320","1290–1317":"1290–1317","1316–1380":"1316–1380","1254–1306":"1254–1306","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","from 1275 to 1306":"from 1275 to 1306","1453":"1453","1288":"1288","1254":"1254","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","Felbrigg, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, Erpingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, England","St. Margaret Churchyard, Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"le","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Thanh, Hung, Minh, Dung, Tuan, Hai, Hoa, Thuy, Son, Anh, Long, Hoang.  Chinese Hong, Sang, Chi, Dong, Tong, Lai, Hang, Man, Han, Ho, Phoung, Chan.  Korean Tam, Phong, Nam, Thai, Tuong, Chung, Thach, Tinh, Manh, Tham, Uyen, Vang.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 樂, meaning ‘happiness’ in Chinese: from the first element of the personal name Le Fu (樂父), style name of Yan, son of the Duke Dai of Song (ruler of the state of Song, reigned 799–766  BC ). Yan's grandson Le Ju (樂莒) inherited Le (樂) as his surname.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 勒: (i) from the second element of the placename Shu-Le (疏勒), an ancient state (located in present-day Xinjiang Uyghur autonomous region) during the Western Han dynasty (206  BC –25  AD ). (ii) a surname near the Bohai Sea region during the Han dynasty (206  BC –220  AD ). (iii) a surname traced back to the Hun ethnic group in northern China during the Jin dynasty (265–420  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Yue","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Chi, Feng, Gang, Wei, Chun, Guo, Jin, Kin, Ping, Yan, Yun, Zhang, Chau, Du, Hau, Hung, My, Sau.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 岳 (or 嶽), meaning ‘high mountain’ in Chinese: traced back to Si Yue (四岳 or 四嶽), said to be the title of an official post in charge of sacrificial rituals on the site of famous mountains during the reign of the legendary Emperor Yao (<i>c.</i> 24th century  BC ) and Emperor Shun (<i>c.</i> 23rd century  BC )."]},{"name":"Lok","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Ping, Tat, Wing, Ying Lin, Chi Ming, Ching Wah, Chun, Chung Man, Han, Kam, Kam Tim, Kin.","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surname 樂, see   Le   1.","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surnames 陸, 鹿, 逯 and 禄, see   Lu   5 and (7-9)."]},{"name":"Li","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Ming, Li, Jian, Hong, Yan, Ping, Jing, Yong, Ying, Hui, Jin, Min, Chung.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 李, meaning ‘plum’: (i) said to have been adopted in place of the Chinese surname 理 (also pronounced Li; meaning ‘rules’ in Chinese) by Li Zhen (利貞), son of an official called Li Zheng (理徵) in the late Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). It is said that Li Zhen's father incurred the displeasure of King Zhou of Shang (died 1046  BC ) and Li Zhen fled to a wasteland area, where he survived on wild plums. After his return to civilization, he changed his surname to Li (李 ‘plum’), a word with the same pronunciation. The original surname, 理, is said to be from Li Guan (理官), the name of a post of officials in charge of legislation in ancient China. Li Er (李耳), also known as Lao Tzu or Lao Zi, traditionally regarded as the founder of Taoism, is believed to have been a descendant of Li Zhen. (ii) adopted as a surname by the Chi Li (叱李) family from the Xianbei ethnic group during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) in the early years of the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ), sixteen high officials with different surnames were granted the surname Li (李), the surname of the royal family of the Tang dynasty, by Emperor Taizong of Tang (died 649  BC ), because of their contributions to the establishment of the Tang regime. (iv) the surname can also be traced back to several minority ethnic groups in ancient China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 黎, meaning ‘black’ or ‘multitude’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from Li (黎), the name of an ancient state (located in Changzhi in Shanxi province) during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ), which was annexed in the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ) and later granted to Fengshu, also known as Li Hou (黎侯, 'Marquis Li'). (ii) adopted as a surname by the Su Li (素黎) family, members of the Xianbei ethnic group, during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD )."]}]},{"name":"Bigod","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Jaroslaw, Jozef, Krystyna, Slawomir.","Polish and Jewish (from Poland): from <i>bigos</i>, formerlydenoting anything that was chopped or slashed, now a particular dishcomposed of hash and sauerkraut; also ‘confusion’; hence perhaps anickname for someone who caused confusion."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Simon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":16,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":41,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":54,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":63,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Simon le Bigod was born in 1274, in Felbrigg, Norfolk, England as the son of Sir Roger Bigod Felbrigge. He married Alice Thorpe in 1315, in Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1351, in Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 77, and was buried in Felbrigg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1274–1351":"1274–1351","1288–1320":"1288–1320","1290–1317":"1290–1317","1316–1380":"1316–1380","1254–1306":"1254–1306","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","from 1275 to 1306":"1275 kuni 1306","1453":"1453","1288":"1288","1254":"1254","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","Felbrigg, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, Erpingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Felbrigg, North Norfolk District, Norfolk, England":"Felbrigg, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, England","St. Marg